                       <h3>What is the HirePortal?</h3>
                        <div>
                         <p>
                          The HirePortal is a website that allows Store Managers from your company to communicate their recruitment needs with Mindfield. 
                          Using the HirePortal, you can create a new Job, view candidates screened by Mindfield for your open Jobs, hire or reject candidates that Mindfield presented, access Live Chat, and find all training materials related to recruitment.
                         </p>
                        </div>
                    
                        <h3>How do I create a new Job using the HirePortal?</h3>
                        <div>
                         <p>
                          From any page of the HirePortal, click the <i>Create a Job</i> button on the left-hand side of your screen.
                          This will take you to a page where you can edit provide details of the job you are looking to fill (job title, availability, etc.).
                          All boxes marked with a red line are required.
                          There are a number of additional boxes and fields that can be filled in as appropriate for your job.
                          Once the <i>Save</i> button is clicked, the job will enter the pre-established job approval process.
                         </p>
                        </div>
                    
                        <h3>How do I post multiple Job as quickly as possible?</h3>
                        <div>
                         <p>
                          To quickly create one Job after another, enter all the details for the first Job and then click <b><i>Save and New</i></b>.
                          This will save your current Job and bring you back to the Open Job page where you can change any job details prior to creating a new job. 
                          Alternatively, if you are posting the exact same Job, you can simply duplicate the job. 
                          To learn to do this, see the help topic <i>“How do I post an identical job Job multiple times using the HirePortal”</i>. 
                         </p>
                        </div>
                        
                        <h3>How do I post an identical Job multiple times?</h3>
                        <div>
                         <p>
                          If you need to post the exact same Job more than once, enter all the details for the first Job and then click <b><i>Save</i></b>. 
                          This will save your current vacancy and bring you right to the screen where you can see the details about the job. 
                          On that screen, click the <b><i>Duplicate</i></b> button and an exact duplicate of that job will be created. 
                          Click <b><i>Save</i></b> and repeat if necessary. 
                         </p>
                        </div>
                        
                        <h3>How will I know when Mindfield has submitted Qualified Candidates for my Job?</h3>
                        <div>
                         <p>
                          There are two ways you will know Mindfield has presented Qualified Candidates:
                          <ol type="1">
                            <li>Hiring Managers will receive a new candidate notification email with the following information associated to a Qualified Candidate:
                                <ol type="a">
                                  <li>Candidate contact information</li>
                                  <li>Customized recruiter summary write-up</li>
                                  <li>Phone interview</li> 
                                  <li>Details on the date/time of the candidates scheduled in-person interview</li>
                                </ol>  
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                From any page of the HirePortal, click <i>View Open Jobs</i> on the left-hand side of your screen. 
                                All open jobs for your store will be displayed. 
                                Click on the “Job ID #” associated with the Job you want to view candidates for and you will be brought to a page that displays all of the candidates submitted for that Job.
                                Select the candidate record by clicking on their name.
                            </li>
                          </ol>
                         </p>
                        </div>
                        
